ed evaluation set of customer questions and score whether answers address intent (human rubric or LLM-as-judge with adjudication), failing if off-topic/generic rate exceeds threshold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The tone re-check correctly identifies when a response is too formal for a casual-tier customer and triggers regeneration.","required_reality_check_level":"Workflow","justification":"LLM-DEP: 'correctly identifies ... too formal' depends on model judgment. MULTI-STEP: requires sequential agentic stages (initial generation -> tone evaluation -> regeneration trigger), so this exceeds single-step Agentic. MOCK-HIDE: stubbing either detection or regeneration hides real misclassification/trigger behavior. REJECTION-GATE: Agentic-only was rejected because the behavior text explicitly includes both detection and subsequent regeneration trigger in sequence.","test_description":"Run end-to-end conversational cases with casual-tier profiles against real model calls, verify first draft is judged too formal by the live tone-check path, then confirm regeneration is invoked and produces an acceptable casual-tier response.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.27,"Workflow":0.65}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full exchange (user message, generated response, any regenerations) is persisted to the database with correct timestamps.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure appears when chat orchestration, regeneration flow, and persistence layer interact (record completeness/order/timestamps). REAL-INFRA: behavior text asks for DB persistence, which can be validated with a real local test DB; no explicit external network/API contract requirement to force System. ROUND-TRIP: readback f